column5: https://fox8.com/2018/10/08/alligator-found-swimming-in-lake-michigan/ They're migrating? Zoom lizards gone wild?

Crazy!  I'm gonna guess it escaped or was release from a reptile zoo or somewhere.  We had a similar situation happen in Hamilton a few years ago.  It made the papers too. And yup, I DID see Lake Placid and it's one of my all-time favourite movies.  Great special effects and funny as hell!

LOL Mike, ya my kind of movie! but the story actual is even crazier, sounds like someone set it out to die with it's mouth tied? shut. http://www.cleveland19.com/video/2018/10/09/fisherman-rescues-foot-alligator-cold-waters-lake-michigan/
It gets stranger and stranger.  It's gonna be interesting to see if they can figure out the story behind that little gator and how it got there.
